,"comments":[],"created_at":1784776523970152001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Problem\nprerequisites.py run_focused_finder emits emit_indeterminate(model=cfg.model) at line ~235, but run_bin escalates up a model ladder (models_at_or_above) on context-limit errors and re-runs on next_model. When escalation fires, the record was produced by the escalated model while the log reports cfg.model — e.g. logs 'claude-haiku-4-5' while the payload ran on 'claude-sonnet-4-6'. attempt_count is also hardcoded 1 at the call site, conveying nothing about retries.\n\n## Root cause (confirmed by reading)\nrun_bin(bin_, model) returns records but does NOT carry the model that produced them; the outer loop reports cfg.model unconditionally. src/rebar/llm/plan_review/prerequisites.py:189-238.\n\n## Fix\nThread the actual model that produced each record through to emit_indeterminate. Either return (records, model_used) from run_bin per record, or stamp the producing model onto each indeterminate record and read it back. Wire attempt_count to the real retry depth or drop the field.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- When run_bin escalates to a higher model, the emitted plan_review_prerequisite_indeterminate log 'model' field equals the escalated model, not cfg.model.\n- A unit test drives an escalation (context-limit error forces next_model) and asserts the logged/emitted model equals the escalated model; asserting cfg.model would FAIL.\n- attempt_count reflects real attempts or is removed (test asserts either the wired value or absence).\n\n## Verification\npytest the new test; assert emitted model == escalated model under a forced escalation.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/prerequisites.py","reason":"emit the model that actually produced the record, not cfg.model"},{"path":"tests/llm/plan_review/test_prerequisites_model_log.py","reason":"RED test: forced escalation asserts escalated model is logged"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","56c0-1d2f-f39c-4ac1"]],"parent_id":"","parent_status_uuid":"7769a997-f664-4525-a030-6ad6af7b7608","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"4e1f-6773-3346-4c48","ticket_type":"bug","title":"plan-review indeterminate log reports configured model, not the model that actually ran","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["b5df3a5d-f844-4af0-a4f6-eb5c253c1ac6","22d7983c-26e4-41bb-8867-0e30ffc98c64","9c19cf94-5ffc-4488-b88d-467845c3f7cd","7769a997-f664-4525-a030-6ad6af7b7608","b2d41e5b-fdab-4f0c-b8ac-dea198b93cdb","e7ae9384-e289-4f22-a225-02d618bbfc3d"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784777127272770205,"uuid":"e87811ce-6ee1-4155-a7c1-3774b38354a2"}